  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and rinse under <strong>cold water </strong>to cool</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-7-1657641974314-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-7-1657641974314-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-7-1657641974314-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-7-1657641974314-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-7-1657641974314-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into thick rounds</p><p>Deseed the<strong> peppers </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into large chunks</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into large wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-7-1657641979071-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-7-1657641979071-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-7-1657641979071-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-7-1657641979071-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-7-1657641979071-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>veg</strong> to a large bowl, drizzle with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>coated</strong> <strong>veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-6-1657641983758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-6-1657641983758-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-6-1657641983758-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-6-1657641983758-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-6-1657641983758-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Thread the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>veg</strong> onto the <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewers</strong>, alternating as you go</p><p>Add the <strong>veg skewers </strong>(and any remaining veg) to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil </strong>to avoid mess!) and reserve the bowl</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>sesame seeds </strong>over the veg skewers</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until everything has browned and is starting to char – these are your<strong> roasted veg skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-7-1657641989669-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-7-1657641989669-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-7-1657641989669-x700.jpg",
